      • children

        public java.util.Set<View> children()
        Provides the set of views that will be rendered within this view. Those child views may have children of their own that won't be included.
        Returns:
        Set populated with all direct children of this view.

      • setParent

        public void setParent​(View view)
        Sets this view's parent view, for cases when we need to climb the view hierarchy. The parent will be referenced weakly to prevent circular references.
        Parameters:
        view - The view that contains this view. May be null if this is a root view.
